https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/037fddf6d3bf6d691a448e01136f233a?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26ownerId%3Dsjones%26avatarId%3D18300%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/037fddf6d3bf6d691a448e01136f233a?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26ownerId%3Dsjones%26avatarId%3D18300%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","32x32":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/037fddf6d3bf6d691a448e01136f233a?s=32&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dmedium%26ownerId%3Dsjones%26avatarId%3D18300%26noRedirect%3Dtrue"},"displayName":"Steve Jones","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"body":"Currently the keys directory has 700 permissions which provides security for private key / secret files. We can make changes to ensure individual files have appropriate permissions for security but making the keys directory world readable does have some security impact.\r\n\r\nFrom eucalyptus RPM:\r\n\r\n{code}\r\ndrwx------    2 eucalypteucalypt                    0 Jun 15 08:04 /var/lib/eucalyptus/keys\r\n-rwxr-xr-x    1 root    root                     2859 Jun 15 08:04 /var/lib/eucalyptus/keys/cc-client-policy.xml\r\n-rwxr-xr-x    1 root    root                     2851 Jun 15 08:04 /var/lib/eucalyptus/keys/sc-client-policy.xml\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nNote that the packaging does not match the permissions that will be set at runtime for the policy files, resulting in verification errors:\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n.M...UG..    /var/lib/eucalyptus/keys/cc-client-policy.xml\r\n.M...UG..    /var/lib/eucalyptus/keys/sc-client-policy.xml\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nHere's the listing of file permissions on a build from source, before and after restarting eucalyptus (first restart):\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n# ll /opt/eucalyptus/var/lib/eucalyptus/keys/\r\ntotal 60\r\n-rwx------ 1 eucalyptus eucalyptus  2957 Sep 16 15:12 cc-client-policy.xml\r\n-rwx------ 1 eucalyptus eucalyptus  1188 Sep 16 15:17 cloud-cert.pem\r\n-rwx------ 1 eucalyptus eucalyptus  1679 Sep 16 15:17 cloud-pk.pem\r\n-rw-r--r-- 1 eucalyptus eucalyptus  1184 Sep 16 15:21 cluster-cert.pem\r\n-rw-r--r-- 1 eucalyptus eucalyptus  1679 Sep 16 15:21 cluster-pk.pem\r\n-rwx------ 1 eucalyptus eucalyptus 14059 Sep 16 15:17 euca.p12\r\n-rwx------ 1 eucalyptus eucalyptus  2959 Sep 16 15:12 nc-client-policy.xml\r\n-rw-r--r-- 1 eucalyptus eucalyptus  1184 Sep 16 15:21 node-cert.pem\r\n-rw-r--r-- 1 eucalyptus eucalyptus  1679 Sep 16 15:21 node-pk.pem\r\ndrwxr-xr-x 2 eucalyptus eucalyptus  4096 Sep 16 15:21 PARTI00\r\n-rwx------ 1 eucalyptus eucalyptus  2949 Sep 16 15:12 sc-client-policy.xml\r\n-rw-r--r-- 1 eucalyptus eucalyptus   512 Sep 16 15:21 vtunpass\r\n# service eucalyptus-cloud restart\r\nStopping Eucalyptus services: done.\r\nStarting Eucalyptus services: done.\r\n# ll /opt/eucalyptus/var/lib/eucalyptus/keys/\r\ntotal 60\r\n-rwx------ 1 eucalyptus eucalyptus  2957 Sep 16 15:12 cc-client-policy.xml\r\n-rwx------ 1 eucalyptus eucalyptus  1188 Sep 16 15:17 cloud-cert.pem\r\n-rwx------ 1 eucalyptus eucalyptus  1679 Sep 16 15:17 cloud-pk.pem\r\n-rwx------ 1 eucalyptus eucalyptus  1184 Sep 16 15:21 cluster-cert.pem\r\n-rwx------ 1 eucalyptus eucalyptus  1679 Sep 16 15:21 cluster-pk.pem\r\n-rwx------ 1 eucalyptus eucalyptus 14059 Sep 16 15:17 euca.p12\r\n-rwx------ 1 eucalyptus eucalyptus  2959 Sep 16 15:12 nc-client-policy.xml\r\n-rwx------ 1 eucalyptus eucalyptus  1184 Sep 16 15:21 node-cert.pem\r\n-rwx------ 1 eucalyptus eucalyptus  1679 Sep 16 15:21 node-pk.pem\r\ndrwx------ 2 eucalyptus eucalyptus  4096 Sep 16 15:21 PARTI00\r\n-rwx------ 1 eucalyptus eucalyptus  2949 Sep 16 15:12 sc-client-policy.xml\r\n-rwx------ 1 eucalyptus eucalyptus   512 Sep 16 15:21 vtunpass\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nSo currently private keys and other secrets would be world readable for a period if the keys directory was more open. This would need to be changed as part of addressing this issue (assuming this issue is addressed by making the keys directory more open)\r\n\r\nIt looks like permissions/ownership are preserved when copying (key/cert) files at registration time with rsync, but not if the scp fallback is used (I have not tested this)\r\n\r\nOn upgrade existing files in the keys directory would need to have their permissions updated, this would have to be done in the packaging if we wanted to avoid a window where files were potentially exposed (though this seems like a small risk, most files would have secure permissions)","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=sjones","name":"sjones","key":"sjones","accountId":"557058:f5dce1b0-db45-4dd6-a0e8-3cea5effb5ce","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/037fddf6d3bf6d691a448e01136f233a?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FownerId%3Dsjones%26avatarId%3D18300%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/037fddf6d3bf6d691a448e01136f233a?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26ownerId%3Dsjones%26avatarId%3D18300%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/037fddf6d3bf6d691a448e01136f233a?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26ownerId%3Dsjones%26avatarId%3D18300%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","32x32":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/037fddf6d3bf6d691a448e01136f233a?s=32&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dmedium%26ownerId%3Dsjones%26avatarId%3D18300%26noRedirect%3Dtrue"},"displayName":"Steve Jones","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"created":"2013-09-17T12:38:33.743-0500","updated":"2013-09-17T12:38:33.743-0500"},{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/issue/23876/comment/53875","id":"53875","author":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=sjones","name":"sjones","key":"sjones","accountId":"557058:f5dce1b0-db45-4dd6-a0e8-3cea5effb5ce","avatarUrl